Prepare AWS Cloud Shell or Any Compute instance to operate EKS cluster
Install latest AWS CLI

curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

unzip awscliv2.zip

sudo ./aws/install

Ref Url: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html

Install eksctl

curl --silent --location "https://github.com/weaveworks/eksctl/releases/latest/download/eksctl_$(uname -s)_amd64.tar.gz" | tar xz -C /tmp

sudo mv /tmp/eksctl /usr/local/bin

eksctl version

Ref Url: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/eksctl.html

Install kubectl

curl -o kubectl https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/amazon-eks/1.22.6/2022-03-09/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl

chmod +x ./kubectl

mkdir -p $HOME/bin && cp ./kubectl $HOME/bin/kubectl && export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/bin

kubectl version --short --client

Ref Url: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/install-kubectl.html Ref URL: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-linux/

Configure cloud shell to access AWS resources

aws configure

aws configure list

Ref Url: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-configure-files.html

Install Gcloud curl -O https://dl.google.com/dl/cloudsdk/channels/rapid/downloads/google-cloud-cli-linux-x86_64.tar.gz tar -xf google-cloud-cli-linux-x86_64.tar.gz ./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh ./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh --help ./google-cloud-sdk/bin/gcloud init ./google-cloud-sdk/bin/gcloud version

